"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM client\nJOIN disp ON client.client_id = disp.client_id\nJOIN account ON disp.account_id = account.account_id\nWHERE account.frequency = 'POPLATEK TYDNE' AND disp.type = 'OWNER';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of clients who have chosen a weekly issuance frequency for their account statements and are designated as \"Owner\" in the disposition table. The query joins the `client`, `disp`, and `account` tables using the foreign key relationships defined in the schema."